-- Stocks Decline in London as Mining, Bank Shares Retreat; Kazakhmys Slides
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-09-23T08:50:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/stocks-decline-in-london-as-mining-bank-shares-retreat-kazakhmys-slides.html
U.K. stocks retreated, led by a
sell off in mining companies and banks shares.  The FTSE 100 Index dropped 0.7 percent to 5,511.45 at 9:44
a.m. in London after earlier climbing as much as 0.7 percent.  Kazakhmys Plc dropped 2.2 percent to 1,409 pence, while
Lloyds Banking Group Plc fell 2.2 percent to 74.16 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  